te, R.M., Barometric tides from ECMWF operational analyses (2003) Ann. Geophys., 21, pp. 1897-1910; Rogers, J.C., Patterns of low-frequency monthly sea level pressure variability (1899-1986) and associated wave cyclone frequencies (1990) J. Climate, 3, pp. 1364-1379; Rogers, J.C., North Atlantic storm track variability and its association to the North Atlantic Oscillation and climate variability of northern Europe (1997) J. Climate, 10, pp. 1635-1647; Schmith, T., Alexandersson, H., Iden, K., Tuomenvirta, H., (1997) North Atlantic-European Pressure Observations 1868-1995 (WASA Dataset Version 1.0), , Danish Meteorological Institute Technical Report 97-3, DMI, Copenhagen; van Loon, H., Rogers, J.C., Seesaw in winter temperatures between Greenland and Northern Europe 1. General description (1978) Mon. Wea. Rev., 106, pp. 296-310; Wang, X.L.L., Zwiers, F.W., Swail, V.R., North Atlantic Ocean wave climate change scenarios for the twenty-first century (2004) J. Climate, 17, pp. 2368-2383; Wanner, H., Brönnimann, S., Casty, C., Gyalistras, D., Luterbacher, J., Schmutz, C., Stephenson, D.B., Xoplaki, E., North Atlantic Oscillation - Concepts and studies (2001) Surv. Geophys., 22, pp. 321-382; (1978) Compendium of Meteorology. Vol. 1. Part 3 - Synoptic Meteorology, 34, p. 276. , Wiin-Nielsen, A. (Ed), WMO, NR. 1978; Zveryaev, I.I., Decadal and longer changes of the winter sea level pressure fields and related synoptic activity over the North Atlantic (1999) Int. J. Climatol., 19, pp. 1177-1185","Jónsson, T.; Icelandic Meteorological Office, Bustadavegur 9, Reykjavík 150, Iceland; email: trausti@vedur.is",,,,,,,,09412948,,MEZEE,,"English","Meteorol. Z.",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-33947430977
